SIMPLE: propine
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Propine
<hw>Pro*pine"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>propinare</ets>, Gr. <?/; <?/ before + <?/ to drink.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To pledge; to offer as a toast or a health in the
manner of drinking, that is, by drinking first and passing the
cup.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The lovely sorceress mixed, and to the prince⟦br⟧
Health, peace, and joy <qex>propined</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>C.
Smart.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, to give in token of friendship.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To give, or deliver; to subject.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Fotherby.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Propine</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Propine
<hw>Pro*pine"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A pledge.</def> <mark>[Obs. or Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A gift; esp., drink money.</def> <mark>[Obs or
Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Propine</ent>⟦br⟧

